<paragraph blockId="10.[151,792,943,1003]" box="[151,336,978,1003]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,288,978,1003]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 22" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,197,1799]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1799]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 22. Species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 1 – 2. A. alstonii. 3 – 4. A. nurtia ludibunda. 5 – 6. A. pulchra. 7 – 8. A. bonita. 9 – 10. A. amalfreda. 11 – 12. A. physis phyton. 13 – 14. A. halli sp. nov. holotype. 15 – 16. A. celata. 17 – 20. A. gallardi sp. nov. 17 – 18. Male holotype. 19 – 20. Female (tentative determination). 21 – 22. A. aparamilla. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233289/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
Figs 
<number box="[215,288,979,1003]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="21.775" valueMax="22.55" valueMin="21.0">21–22</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[299,328,978,1003]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 55" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1434,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 55. Male genitalia of species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 46. A. alstonii. 47. A. nurtia ludibunda. 48. A. pulchra. 49. A. bonita. 50. A. amalfreda. 51. A. physis phyton. 52. A. halli sp. nov. paratype. 53. A. celata. 54. A. gallardi sp. nov. paratype from PNSD. 55. A. aparamilla. Left to right: dorsal view of uncus, lateral view of tegumen, saccus, uncus, gnathos, valva and aedeagus, and ventral view of valva. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233292/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">55</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1050,1402]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
Two males of this distinctive species were collected at 
<collectionCode box="[795,867,1051,1075]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">PNSD</collectionCode>
in 
<date box="[910,1086,1050,1075]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="2013" valueMax="2014">
<number box="[910,966,1051,1075]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="2013.0">2013</number>
and 
<number box="[1026,1086,1051,1075]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="2014.0">2014</number>
</date>
. The male found in 
<number box="[1326,1382,1051,1075]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="2013.0">2013</number>
was captured while flying in a small sun patch at the hilltop, about one meter of the ground, around 
<number box="[1263,1291,1086,1111]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="14.0">14</number>
: 
<number box="[1295,1325,1086,1111]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="30.0">30</number>
h with an aberrant male of 
<taxonomicName box="[339,442,1122,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bonita">
<emphasis box="[339,442,1122,1147]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">A. bonita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen found in 
<number box="[716,772,1123,1147]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="2014.0">2014</number>
was collected while resting on the underside of a leaf about two meters from the ground around 
<number box="[555,583,1158,1183]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="15.0">15</number>
:00h.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1050,1402]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
The males of 
<taxonomicName box="[352,507,1194,1219]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aparamilla">
<emphasis box="[352,507,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">A. aparamilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found at 
<collectionCode box="[614,686,1195,1219]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">PNSD</collectionCode>
are the second record known for this species, which was described from a single male collected in similar elevation in eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[807,903,1230,1255]" name="Ecuador" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. The color pattern of the specimens from 
<collectionCode box="[1365,1436,1231,1255]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">PNSD</collectionCode>
differs in some aspects of the 
<typeStatus box="[498,596,1266,1291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[638,795,1266,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aparamilla">
<emphasis box="[638,795,1266,1291]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">A. aparamilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mainly by the addition of a blue spot in M 
<number box="[1304,1312,1281,1295]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="3.0">3</number>
–CuA 
<number box="[1379,1387,1281,1295]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="1.0">1</number>
and reduction of the orange on the forewing upperside, and the underside of both wings with the black spots more developed. However, the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[617,700,1341,1366]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 55" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1434,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 55. Male genitalia of species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 46. A. alstonii. 47. A. nurtia ludibunda. 48. A. pulchra. 49. A. bonita. 50. A. amalfreda. 51. A. physis phyton. 52. A. halli sp. nov. paratype. 53. A. celata. 54. A. gallardi sp. nov. paratype from PNSD. 55. A. aparamilla. Left to right: dorsal view of uncus, lateral view of tegumen, saccus, uncus, gnathos, valva and aedeagus, and ventral view of valva. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233292/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
Fig. 
<number box="[671,700,1341,1366]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="55.0">55</number>
</figureCitation>
) is similar to that figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[1035,1396,1341,1366]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1995) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, with descriptions of five new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 6, 136 - 143." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hall &amp; Willmott (
<number box="[1239,1298,1341,1366]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="1995.0">1995</number>
, fig. 
<number box="[1358,1387,1341,1366]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="16.0">16</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for the 
<typeStatus box="[192,290,1377,1402]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[327,482,1377,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aparamilla">
<emphasis box="[327,482,1377,1402]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">A. aparamilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
